⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Maria the Jewess
node ALC · ALC · ⟦Maria the Jewess:ALC:4ce8e8⟧

WHO   — Maria the Jewess — the instrument-maker · c. 1st–3rd c.
WHAT  — The great apparatus-builder: she is credited with the tribikos still, the kerotakis, and the gentle water-bath — the bain-marie that still bears her name.
WHERE — ALC · The Great Work  Framework inputs: Alchemy, catalogued by ROOT0  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because her instruments outlived every theory; real chemistry inherited her hardware directly.
HOW   — By inventing and describing distillation and heating apparatus, and the axiom ‘one becomes two, two becomes three, and out of the third comes the one as the fourth.’

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  They forgot my theories and kept my instruments — my water-bath still warms the world by my name.

